{
  "stem": "16503.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 258.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was a closed ghetto, meaning that people were in their accommodation, working, taken by the-- by the military to-- to whatever they were working at, and then brought back into the-- into their accommodation.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But when I came to-- to Theresienstadt, it became an open ghetto, meaning that you could walk the streets to a certain time of the day.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were-- as I said, the ghetto was naturally-- had a boundary.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But then, they had-- then the things like for a train, where the street, you could have walked out of, so that was guarded, of course.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And really, I think the Germans have established Theresienstadt as a-- as a showcase of-- of their [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] war [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] ability of dealing with Jews.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were notified about four days before, where we had to go and get to the assembly place.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, we are going back to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Jewish community and the SS.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you see, my father not being a able-bodied person, they said that my family has got to-- that two of us, like the girls have got to go and mother and father can stay in Prague for another period of time.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody knew for how long.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- but because of the Jewish community, and they had some say in it I presume, they-- my mother objected, saying that, you know, she is not going to send two young girls away, and that she will go with me, because I was the youngest.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my sister, who was 16 by then, would be a help to my father.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she will stay with him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's how it finished.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I went with my mother in July of 1942 to Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
